":"reccZB8SVU5bEMcgo","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"rec2OlshepuMiuLDJ","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"recqDQWQP9P7218TS","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"rec0BAacWSGBXZ0zI","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"reci5XsSfPw9RZWBA","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"rec0rm6yYA4YUQrkh","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"rec48avi3AS18d5V6","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"recq9ttBUfBJW1lhG","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"recL1WV82pXaRBQ59","label":"mentions"},{"source":"recn9sbuzqAtgp8Sz","target":"reczzYTmzPPDcP3qv","label":"event"}],"verses":[{"id":"recxC54qedz4vJlWg","ref":"2Sam.12.1","text":"And the LORD sent Nathan unto David. And he came unto him, and said unto him, There were two men in one city; the one rich, and the other poor.","year":-1034},{"id":"recuNoBpo9sd8XQK8","ref":"2Sam.12.2","text":"The rich man had exceeding many flocks and herds:","year":-1034},{"id":"recYE5AXfyxkPkmti","ref":"2Sam.12.3","text":"But the poor man had nothing, save one little ewe lamb, which he had bought and nourished up: and it grew up together with him, and with his children; it did eat of his own meat, and drank of his own cup, and lay in his bosom, and was unto him as a daughter.","year":-1034},{"id":"reclKJqO1bheLt0yE","ref":"2Sam.12.4","text":"And there came a traveller unto the rich man, and he spared to take of his own flock and of his own herd, to dress for the wayfaring man that was come unto him; but took the poor man’s lamb, and dressed it for the man that was come to him.","year":-1034},{"id":"recZxGpbJlLgodcI2","ref":"2Sam.12.5","text":"And David’s anger was greatly kindled against the man; and he said to Nathan, As the LORD liveth, the man that hath done this thing shall surely die:","year":-1034},{"id":"recE3prLjsLdwMAG5","ref":"2Sam.12.6","text":"And he shall restore the lamb fourfold, because he did this thing, and because he had no pity.","year":-1034},{"id":"recGDizyxzOKcXEcR","ref":"2Sam.12.7","text":"And Nathan said to David, Thou art the man. Thus saith the LORD God of Israel, I anointed thee king over Israel, and I delivered thee out of the hand of Saul;","year":-1034},{"id":"recqYRUvG6qwmC8mO","ref":"2Sam.12.8","text":"And I gave thee thy master’s house, and thy master’s wives into thy bosom, and gave thee the house of Israel and of Judah; and if that had been too little, I would moreover have given unto thee such and such things.","year":-1034}]}
